As a user,
I want to enter my ZIP code to view applicable account rates,
so that I can see accurate, location‑specific information before deciding to open an account.

Details
The Rates component displays:

A section heading (e.g., “Checking Account Rates*”)

A Lable above the input field 

A ZIP code input field

A primary action button (e.g., “View Rates”)

The rates table is hidden by default

Rates are displayed only after a ZIP code is entered and submitted

Rates shown are location‑specific and may vary by ZIP code 

The component supports:

Client‑side validation of ZIP code

Dynamic rendering of rates

Each rate row may include:

Account type

APY

Minimum to open

CTA link (e.g., “Open an account”)

Search for rates from Middleware (API integration) using zip code as input.

Developer Note: All validations should be performed on both the client side and the server side. A possible validation for a ZIP code can use the following RegEx:
zipCodeRegex = /^\d{5}(-\d{4})?$/;

Desktop 

ZIP code input and button appear inline near the section heading

Rates display in a tabular layout after ZIP submission

Table headers remain visible while scanning rows

CTAs appear within the table rows

Mobile 

ZIP code input and button stack vertically

Rates display in a stacked, card‑style layout (one account per block)

Each account block includes:

Account name

APY

Minimum to open

CTA link

 

