Acceptance Criteria
Desktop

Given the page is viewed on a desktop viewport
When the Rates component is rendered
Then the ZIP code input and “View Rates” button are displayed
And the rates table is not displayed

Given the ZIP code input is displayed
When the user enters a 5‑digit ZIP code
Then the ZIP code value is accepted

Given the ZIP code input is displayed
When the user enters an invalid ZIP code format and clicks “View Rates”
Then the rates table is not displayed and an inline validation message is shown

Given a valid ZIP code is entered
When the user clicks the “View Rates” button
Then the rates table is displayed below the input
And the table shows account‑specific data for that ZIP code

Given the rates table is displayed
When account data is returned
Then each row displays:

Account type

APY

Minimum to open

“Open an account” CTA

Given an “Open an account” link is displayed in a table row
When the user clicks the CTA
Then the user is navigated to the corresponding account opening page

Given rates are currently displayed
When the user enters a different valid ZIP code
And clicks “View Rates”
Then the rates table updates to reflect the new ZIP code

Mobile

Given the page is viewed on a mobile device
When the Rates component is rendered
Then the ZIP code input and “View Rates” button are displayed
And no rates are displayed initially

Given a valid ZIP code is entered on mobile
When the user taps the “View Rates” button
Then the rates content is displayed below the input

Given rates are displayed on mobile
When the component renders
Then each account is displayed as a stacked block
And each block includes:

Account name

APY

Minimum to open

“Open an account” CTA

Given an “Open an account” CTA is displayed
When the user taps the CTA
Then the user is navigated to the corresponding account opening page

Given the user enters an invalid ZIP code
When the user taps “View Rates”
Then the rates are not displayed
And an inline validation message is shown

Accessibility

Given a screen reader is enabled
When the Rates (Dynamic) component is read
Then the section heading is announced first
And the ZIP code input is announced with its label
And the “View Rates” button is announced as an actionable control

Given the rates table is displayed on desktop
When it is read by a screen reader
Then column headers are announced as headers
And row data is announced in the correct column context

Given the user navigates using a keyboard
When focus moves through the component
Then the ZIP code input, “View Rates” button, and CTAs are all focusable

Given any interactive element receives focus
When focus is applied
Then a visible focus indicator is displayed

Given the Rates (Dynamic) component is displayed
When viewed under accessibility contrast settings
Then all text, inputs, buttons, and rate values remain readable


